article.headline: VMI 93, Charleston Southern 90
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Austin Kenon had 26 points and Virginia Military Institute held off Charleston Southern 93-90 on Monday night. VMI (12-2) has won eight straight games and 11 of its past 12. The Keydets are 4-0 in the Big South Conference for the first time since the 1976-77 season. Willie Bell hit 3 of 4 free throws in the final 29 seconds for VMI and Omar Carter missed two tying 3-point attempts in the last 10 seconds. The Keydets led 44-43 at halftime, then the Buccaneers had an 8-2 spurt to lead 51-46. Tied at 72 with 7:50 left, VMI used a 12-5 run to pull ahead for good, although Charleston Southern (5-8, 1-2) cut the lead to two points three times in the last 45 seconds. Hunter Houston added 18 points and Bell had 17 for the Keydets, who hit 15 of 37 3-pointers. Jamarco Warren led six Buccaneers in double figures with 22 points.
